          },
          {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "text": "Multiple Intelligence Theory, developed by Howard Gardner in 1983, revolutionized our understanding of human intelligence. Rather than viewing intelligence as a single, fixed entity measured by IQ tests, Gardner proposed that humans possess at least eight distinct types of intelligence."
          },
